>What is danmei?
Chinese BL novels. Often associated with long-haired swordfighting pretty boys, however there's a myriad of different genres available, from wuxia and xianxia to modern crime thrillers to historical political dramas.

>Where do I start?
Check out Mo Xiang Tong Xiu's novels (The Scum Villain's Self-Saving System, Grandmaster of Demonic Cultivation, Heaven Official's Blessing) for the aforementioned sword boys.
Other popular authors are Priest, Meatbun Doesn't Eat Meat, and Meng Xi Shi.

RULES (PLEASE READ THEM):

1) Be polite to the drawfriends - they're drawing for you, after all.

2) Specifics, details and references pics are always appreciated, and increase the likelihood of your request being fulfilled.

3) Don't expect your request to be done straight away, or even at all - not every request is going to get done. If you think it's been overlooked, wait a while and relink or repost it.

4) Stick to fictional characters.

5) No nsfw requests. Stuff like that belongs in >>>/y/drawthread

6) Please limit image posting to references and request fills. We don't need a bunch of reaction pictures and such killing the thread early.

BOORU LINK: http://cm-drawthread.booru.org/

IMPORTANT NOTICE: Currently Fireden archive isn't working and Archived.moe doesn't save full images, so be sure to upload all deliveries to the booru before the thread archives! Happy requesting and drawing, folks!

Main character of the Legend of Zelda series. He started off with silly designs somewhat based off Peter Pan and eventually morphed into its own when a designer made him sexier as an adult for Ocarina of Time. From here they just kept making the adult versions of him hotter and hotter.

He's adorable, looks-wise. He's a brave young man with a beautiful toned body, slightly shy but not awkward, and just a good person overall. He stands up for the weak but not in a weird anime hero way, just in the way that a real person would. His silence is part of the charm, confident enough to not have to constantly talk to show his feelings. And the idea of being a traveler in medieval times just lends to all sorts of cool scenarios that could be dreamy or romantic.
>What are some of his favorite things?
Link loves food, all kinds. He loves to be with people and to be helpful. He loves exploring, camping, but also enjoys times to relax in something bougie for a night or two. com:
In traditional indigenous Ainu marriages, People who marry in their own villages are all called uiriwak, ‘blood relations,’ ‘brethren,’ but those who marry OUTSIDE their villages are called uiritak, i.e. ‘relation taken away,’ or ‘distant relations,’ ‘brethren brought in.’

Soon after marriage the bridegroom makes a knife sheath, a spoon, a shuttle and weaving loom, and presents them to his bride. This little ceremony is called mat-eikara, i.e. ‘making my wife.’ The bride then makes a girdle, a pair of leggings, a necklace, and a head-dress, which she presents to her husband; this is called hoku eikara, i.e. ‘making my husband.’
